<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id80cde01b-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s8726"><num value="8726">§ 8726.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Amounts necessary to carry out this subchapter may be appropriated from money in the Treasury not otherwise appropriated and from any appropriate appropriation law, except the annual District of Columbia Appropriation Act.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id80cde01c-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/217">Pub. L. 107–217</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1224">116 Stat. 1224</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
